# Summary: Tmux related commands

## direnv in run-shell scripts

Commands bound to keys run via `tmux run-shell`, which uses a non-interactive
shell with no direnv hook, so `.envrc` files never load automatically. Scripts
that act on a git repo must load direnv themselves via the shared helper:

    source "${_DEV_ROOT}/lib/direnv.sh"

- Pane-repo command (acts on the current pane's repo): call `load_direnv` at the
  top. Keypress run-shell already starts in the pane's directory.
- Session-project command (acts on `DEV_PROJECT`): `cd "$WORKSPACE/$project"`
  first, then call `load_direnv`.
